Related: boot, net, PXE
Wake On Lan

sf.net/projects/gkernel >>EthTool (ethtool is a small utility for examining and tuning your ethernet-based network interface.)

scyld.com and Packages.debian.org/sid/etherwake >>A little tool to send magic Wake-on-LAN packets

WayqOnLan.sf.net >>wayqonlan (Wake You On Lan) Wakeonlan front end. Be able to monitor computers' state (On/Off), turn them on, monitor some management services (telnet, ssh, vnc, remote desktop) and start a session in any of them, all in a single application.

http://gsd.di.uminho.pt/jpo/software/wakeonlan >>Wakeonlan is a Perl script that sends 'magic packets' to wake-on-LAN enabled ethernet adapters and motherboards, in order to switch on remote computers.

Wake-On-LAN.sf.net >>WOL implements Wake On LAN functionality in a small program. It wakes up hardware that is Magic Packet compliant.

Wopy.sf.net >>Wopy is yet another Wake on LAN/WAN tool, that allow a computer to be turned on or woken up remotely by a network message sent usually on another computer on the network.

SS-WOLScheduler.sf.net >>This collection of utilities allow scheduled computer shutdowns and startups. Configuration, reporting, and installation is centralized allowing network operators to cut energy usage. Uses WOL (Wake-On-LAN) and WMI for operation.